{
  "stem": "10572.6",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And then when things started, when the temperature got hot in New York, they told me that they were closing up because all of their customers went to the sea and into the mountains.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they would reopen on-- after Labor Day, I could have my job back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But in the meantime, I had to live.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I had been-- it was stupid of me-- too proud to go to an aid agency.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I had felt that I was now on my own.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And after I was there for about four weeks, I got a letter from my father that they needed $700 for the passage, for the steamship, because the American steamship lines wouldn't accept the German money anymore.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so I thought in those days that the problems of yesterday became very small with the problems that I had to face then.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I was without a job.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I had to wait until after Labor Day, if I could survive that long.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then I finally buried my pride and went to a Jewish aid-- the refugee committee.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they told me that they wanted to get me out of New York.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a concentration, and they wanted to disperse us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And would I be willing to go to Elkhart, Indiana?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was at that point ready to go anywhere.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I went on the Greyhound Bus to Elkhart, Indiana.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was a wonderful guy, met me the Greyhound Bus Station, Orry-- Orry Goldberg, who owned the men's store in town.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was Mr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Refugee Committee.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He greeted me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the shock was kind of tremendous, after New York-- Elkhart.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
